<p>Welcome to the web site created for YOU, by your Home Owners Association.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> Give us a piece of your mind.&nbsp;Want to see something particular here?&nbsp;<br /><a title="Feedback" href="#Feedback">Send us your feedback anonymously.</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /> Got a garage sale coming up?&nbsp;Looking to make extra money babysitting?&nbsp;<br /><a title="Classified" href="#Classified">Try our classifieds section.</a>&nbsp;<br /><br /> Help us keep you up to date. <a title="Profile update" href="#Profile">Update your contact info here.</a> <br /> Thanks to those of you that have already taken the time to give us your updated profile.&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>9/28/2013</strong><br /><a href="http://www.scntx.com/articles/2013/09/24/news_update/0611.txt" target="_blank">Lake Ralph Hall approved</a><br /><br /> <strong>9/8/2013</strong><br /> Waterford Park Estates Neighborhood Night Out <strong>FIESTA!</strong> <br />When: Tuesday, Oct 1ST: &nbsp;6-8 P.M. <br />Where: Garwood Cul-De-Sac <br />Catered by: ROSAS CAF&Eacute; <br />Bring Your Favorite Dessert! <br />Bring a lawn chair! <br /><br /><strong>9/7/2013</strong><br />A new website format was introduced that allows residents more control over the content. Navigate to <a href="http://waterfordparkestates.com/admin/" target="_blank">WaterfordParkEstates.com/Admin</a> to propose your changes. Two caveats: #1 - You must have registered on the site in order to use the admin section. &nbsp;A resident name, address, and email address are required. &nbsp;#2 - Changes from the admin site will be posted to a staging area for review. &nbsp;Once the changes are approved, they will be moved to the normal site. &nbsp;Google Chrome or Internet Explorer v10 are recommended.</p>
<p><strong>9/3/2013</strong> <a href="http://www.crosstimbersgazette.com/index.php/local-news/3579-flower-mound-police-probe-daytime-burglaries" target="_blank"><br />Flower Mound police probe daytime burglaries</a><br /><br /><strong>8/31/2013</strong> <br /><a href="http://www.coppellgazette.com/articles/2013/08/31/flower_mound_leader/news/869.txt" target="_blank">Flower Mound mayor concerned about TxDOT road proposal</a><br /><br /><strong>8/27/2013</strong> <br /><a href="http://www.flowermoundleader.com/articles/2013/08/27/flower_mound_leader/news/877.txt" target="_blank">Officials remind residents to be proactive against West Nile virus</a><br /><br /><strong>8/22/2013</strong><br /><a href="http://www.crosstimbersgazette.com/index.php/opinion/3554-denton-county-taxes-going-up" target="_blank">Denton County taxes going up </a><br /><br /><strong>7/29/2013</strong> <br />The results of the vote to annex the new development on the North side of Waterford Park into the existing HOA are as follows:</p>
<p>25 in Favor <br />71 Against</p>
<p>In order to pass, 89 homeowners must have voted in favor, therefore, the annexation will NOT move forward.&nbsp; Thank you to all the homeowners who took the time to vote on this issue.</p>
